<section id="faq" class="bg-slate-50 py-24">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-6 lg:px-8">
    <h2 class="text-center text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-slate-900 sm:text-4xl">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <div class="mx-auto mt-12 max-w-3xl space-y-6">
      <details class="rounded-xl border border-slate-100 bg-white p-6" open>
        <summary class="cursor-pointer text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900">How do point deductions work?</summary>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-600">
          After public launch, setting up campsite monitors will be free. Points will be deducted only after CampSoon helps you successfully book a campsite. Each successful booking uses exactly 1,000 points.
        </p>
      </details>

      <details class="rounded-xl border border-slate-100 bg-white p-6">
        <summary class="cursor-pointer text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900">Where do purchases happen?</summary>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-600">
          After public launch, CampSoon point packages will be purchased inside the CampSoon Chrome extension through Stripe Checkout. This website explains the service, pricing, and policies, but it does not collect payments.
        </p>
      </details>

      <details class="rounded-xl border border-slate-100 bg-white p-6">
        <summary class="cursor-pointer text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900">What does CampSoon monitor?</summary>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-600">
          CampSoon is designed to monitor supported public reservation systems, starting with BC Parks, and alert you when a matching campsite may become available. Availability can change quickly, and CampSoon cannot guarantee that a campsite will remain available or that a reservation will be completed.
        </p>
      </details>

      <details class="rounded-xl border border-slate-100 bg-white p-6">
        <summary class="cursor-pointer text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900">Who charges park reservation fees?</summary>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-600">
          CampSoon will charge only for CampSoon point packages. Any campsite reservation fees, taxes, or official booking charges are charged by the park reservation provider under that provider's own checkout, rules, and policies.
        </p>
      </details>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
